The paper discusses the use of MapReduce-based systems for large-scale data processing, which is a topic related to databases (cs.DB), distributed computing (cs.DC), and data structures (cs.DS). The focus on interactive analysis and query-like programming frameworks suggests information retrieval (cs.IR) as another likely category. Finally, the paper also discusses the creation of a benchmark, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE).
